Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
American College of Gastroenterology Guidelines Update: Diagnosis and Management of Celiac Disease.
These patients require a systematic workup to rule out specific conditions that may cause persistent or recurrent symptoms, especially unintentional gluten contamination. Refractory CD is a rare cause of nonresponsive CD often associated with poor prognosis.
